Differential diagnosis — The new species is most similar to
P. athiasae ( Wicht, 1970 )
by the presence of three pairs of setae on coxal fields I, two pairs of setae on coxal fields II, subequal setae v 1 and v 2 and well-developed ap5. The new species can be distinguished from the latter in having one-chambered stigmata (two-chambered P. in
athiasae
), by smooth setae e (setae e barbed in
P. athiasae
), by the absence of seta on trochanter IV (trochanter IV with seta in
P. athiasae
), and distinctly shorter dorsal body setae (dorsal body setae distinctly longer in
P. athiasae
).
